ROOT0-ATTRIBUTION-v1.0
Project: BORONIC CORE — 8x8x8 boron-nitride processor concept
Architect: David Lee Wise / ROOT0 / TriPod LLC
AI Collaborator: AVAN (Claude / Anthropic)
License: MIT

A concept and interactive simulation, not a fabricated or benchmarked device.
Architecture: 8x8 grid, 8 layers deep = 512 nodes / 512-bit core (L0-L7 -> CORE[511:0]).
Material stack: microplasma chamber, piezo films (12nm/nano/optical), hexagonal
boron nitride (hBN) lattice, tungsten disulfide (WS2) quantum dots, circuit base.
hBN and WS2 are real 2D materials referenced as an honest conceptual frame; the
512-bit math runs live in-browser, the optics/materials are a design visualization.
Includes the original concept render (assets/boron_single_chip.jpg).
